<item>
            <title>[LU-17615] DNE3: &apos;lfs getdirstripe -y DIR&apos; does not print YAML output for directories</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17615</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs getdirstripe -y &lt;em&gt;DIR&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; does not print YAML-formatted output for a striped directory:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs getdirstripe -y /mnt/testfs/dir4
lmv_stripe_count: 4
lmv_stripe_offset: 0
lmv_hash_type: fnv_1a_64
mdtidx           FID[seq:oid:ver]
     0           [0x200000400:0x4:0x0]  
     2           [0x280000403:0x4:0x0]  
     3           [0x2c0000401:0x4:0x0]  
     1           [0x240000403:0x4:0x0]  
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This should print proper YAML-formatted information about the MDT object FIDs, similar to what &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs getstripe -y &lt;em&gt;FILE&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; does for regular files:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs getstripe -y /mnt/testfs/etc/hosts
lmm_stripe_count:  1
lmm_stripe_size:   1048576
lmm_pattern:       raid0
lmm_layout_gen:    0
lmm_stripe_offset: 2
lmm_objects:
      - l_ost_idx: 2
        l_fid:     0x380000403:0xd:0x0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this is also a bit confusing because &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs getdirstripe &lt;em&gt;DIR&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; on an unstriped directory does not print any MDT object FIDs for &lt;tt&gt;&lt;em&gt;DIR&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs getdirstripe -v /mnt/testfs/dir
lmv_stripe_count: 0 lmv_stripe_offset: 3 lmv_hash_type: none
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is inconsistent with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs getstripe &lt;em&gt;FILE&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; which prints OST object information for files even if they only have a single stripe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;yaml&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; option is currently broken, it would be OK to have this print out the MDT object FIDs for unstriped directories.  Similarly, &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs getdirstripe &amp;#45;v&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; doesn&apos;t appear to do anything for directories, so it should also be changed to print the MDT object FIDs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
